{"title_page": "Callio", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n|name=Callio Pyh\u00e4salmi\n|coordinates={{coord|63.659902|N|26.041062|E|display=inline,title}}\n|pushpin_map=Finland\n|pushpin_map_caption=Location in [[Northern Ostrobothnia]] in [[Finland]]\n|image_skyline=Pyhasalmi_mine_old_tower_and_surroundings.jpg\n|image_caption=Old tower and surrounding buildings of Pyh\u00e4salmi mine\n}}\n\n'''Callio''' is a project to oversee the reuse of the [[Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine]], located in the [[Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvi|town of Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvi]] in [[Finland]]. Callio aims to make Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine an operating environment for businesses and an [[underground facility|underground research facility]].\n\nCallio is a joint project by the town of Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvi and the [[University of Oulu]]. In 2017 the facility joined the \"Baltic Sea Underground Facilities and Innovation Network\" ([http://bsuin.eu/ BSUIN]).<ref name=\":9\">{{Cite news|url=https://projects.interreg-baltic.eu/projects/bsuin-102.html|title=BSUIN|work=Interreg Baltic Sea Region \u2013 Project Library|access-date=2018-03-02|language=de}}</ref><ref name=\":3\">{{Cite news|url=https://calliolab.com/underground-laboratories-platforms-innovation-new-businesses-international-research-group-meeting-pyhajarvi-finland/|title=Underground Laboratories|date=2017-09-26|work=Callio Lab|access-date=2018-03-02|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.kaleva.fi/uutiset/pohjois-suomi/pyhajarvi-paasi-mukaan-kaivosyhteistyohon-jossa-kehitetaan-maanalaisia-laboratorioita/771611/|title=Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvi p\u00e4\u00e4si mukaan kaivosyhteisty\u00f6h\u00f6n, jossa kehitet\u00e4\u00e4n maanalaisia laboratorioita|last=Rahko|first=Pekka|date=September 26, 2017|work=Kaleva.fi|access-date=2018-03-02|language=fi}}</ref>\n\nThe word \u201dcallio\u201d is an [[Anglicisation|anglicised]] version of the Finnish word \u201dkallio\u201d [kael-lee-oh], meaning crystalline [[bedrock]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/kallio|title=kallio - Wiktionary|website=en.wiktionary.org|language=en|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kielitoimistonsanakirja.fi/kallio|title=kallio - Kielitoimiston sanakirja|last=|first=|date=|website=www.kielitoimistonsanakirja.fi|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://webxicon.org/search.php?id=91951|title=kallio from Finnish to all languages|last=|first=|date=|website=webxicon.org|language=en|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref>\n\n== Facilities and access ==\nCallio is an umbrella organization for a variety of non-mining activities in and around the mine. Of these, '''Callio Lab'''<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://calliolab.com/|title=Callio Lab|last=|first=|date=|website=Callio Lab|language=en-US|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref> oversees scientific research and development. Proposed new activities include a secure underground [[data center]], pumped hydroelectrical [[Pumped-storage hydroelectricity|energy storage]], plant and fungus growing laboratories, breeding sites for insects and fish, and several other types of underground businesses.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.iltalehti.fi/kotimaa/201801302200704544_u0.shtml|title=Euroopan syvin kaivos lopettaa Pyh\u00e4salmella|last=Jokinen|first=Juha Veli|date=January 29, 2018|work=Ilta-Sanomat|access-date=2018-03-02|language=fi-FI}}</ref><ref name=\":8\">{{Cite web|url=http://callio.info/|title=Callio|last=|first=|date=|website=Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rven Callio|language=en-US|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref>\n\nAs of 2018,<ref name=\":3\" /><ref name=\":4\" /> there are four environmentally controlled laboratories in Callio. Listed top-to-bottom, they are:\n* Lab 1 at 75 m level (245&nbsp;ft depth), occupied by the EMMA experiment;\n* Lab 4 at 660&nbsp;m (2165&nbsp;ft);\n* Lab 3 at 990&nbsp;m (3250&nbsp;ft);\n* Lab 2 at 1430&nbsp;m (4690&nbsp;ft), 120 m<sup>2</sup>, height \u22489 m, currently occupied by the Callio Edible Insects from Mine project<ref name=\":10\" />.\n* Numerous additional service, storage and maintenance halls exist along the access tunnel. \nThe ambient temperature within the mine depends on the depth but is otherwise constant. At the Lab 4 (660 m) level it is 15&nbsp;\u00b0C (59&nbsp;\u00b0F) and at Lab 2 (1430 m) level 28&nbsp;\u00b0C (82&nbsp;\u00b0F).<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=https://yle.fi/uutiset/3-9971777|title=Suomalaisen kaivoksen tunneleissa 660 metrin syvyydess\u00e4 kasvaa perunaa \u2013 \"T\u00e4m\u00e4 mullistaa ruoantuotantoa maailmalla\"|last=Juopperi|first=Hanna|date=December 15, 2017|website=Yle Uutiset|language=fi|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref>\n[[File:Emma koe.JPG|thumb|Measurement station of [[Centre for Underground Physics in Pyh\u00e4salmi|EMMA]], one of the longest-standing experiments in the Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine.]]\nCurrently (2018) the mine harbors two scientific experiments: [[Centre for Underground Physics in Pyh\u00e4salmi|C14 liquid scintillator]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://callio.info/callio-lab/c14-experiment/|title=C14 Experiment|work=Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rven Callio|access-date=2018-03-02|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=\":7\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.nupecc.org/presentations/engvist_jun14.pdf|title=Astroparticle Physics in the Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine|last=Enqvist|first=Timo|date=June 13, 2014|website=www.nupecc.org|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref> and [[Centre for Underground Physics in Pyh\u00e4salmi|EMMA]],<ref name=\":7\" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://callio.info/callio-lab/emma-experiment/|title=EMMA experiment|work=Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rven Callio|access-date=2018-03-02|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.symmetrymagazine.org/article/1000-meters-below|title=1,000 meters below|last=Shivni|first=Rashmi|date=May 31, 2016|work=symmetry magazine|access-date=2018-03-02|language=en}}</ref> operated by [[Centre for Underground Physics in Pyh\u00e4salmi|CUPP]], [[University of Oulu]] and [[University of Jyv\u00e4skyl\u00e4]].\n\n=== Access ===\nThe \"main level\" of the mine is at 1400 meters depth, and is equipped with service and social facilities, e.g., a restaurant and the deepest sauna in the world.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://diepresse.com/home/leben/reise/5201433/FinnlandSauna_Hitze-Bier-und-Birkenzweige|title=Finnland-Sauna: Hitze, Bier und Birkenzweige|last=Knoller|first=Rasso|date=April 18, 2017|work=Die Presse|access-date=2018-03-02|language=de}}</ref> Accessing the main level from the surface takes just 3 minutes using the elevator (average speed 8&nbsp;m/s, maximum 12&nbsp;m/s).<ref name=\":4\" /> The same descent takes about 30 minutes by car, along the 11&nbsp;km long decline access tunnel.<ref name=\":8\" />\n\n== Activities ==\nRecently the mine has opened up for a variety of cultural activities. It has hosted the deepest concert in the world (by [[Agonizer]] at 1271 m ) as well as dance performances.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/world-records/deepest-concert-underground|title=Deepest concert underground|date=August 4, 2007|work=Guinness World Records|access-date=2018-03-02|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://kp24.fi/uutiset/310558/tanssi-tila-ja-luonto-yhdistyvat-laguna-lahempana-sydanta|title=Tanssi, tila ja luonto yhdistyv\u00e4t: Laguna - L\u00e4hemp\u00e4n\u00e4 syd\u00e4nt\u00e4|date=July 24, 2012|work=KP24|access-date=2018-03-02|language=fi-FI}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.liikekieli.com/archives/4647|title=Kuvia Petri Kekonin Lagunasta T\u00e4ydenkuun tansseilta|last=Lamberg|first=Veera|date=August 7, 2012|work=Liikekieli.com|access-date=2018-03-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160417100528/http://www.liikekieli.com/archives/4647|archive-date=April 17, 2016|url-status=dead|language=fi}}</ref> The 11&nbsp;km long spiral-shaped main tunnel has also seen several uphill running and cycling competitions.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://hikisetsiivut.blogspot.fi/2013/11/pyhajarven-alto-de-langliru.html|title=Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rven Alto de L'Angliru|last=Ovaska|first=Kimmo|date=November 3, 2013|website=hikisetsiivut.blogspot.fi|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref><ref>Youtube video: {{Citation|last=Pohti SkiTeam|title=Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvi Tour Trailer mp4|date=2016-08-16|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EpONbrTo77E|accessdate=2018-03-02}}</ref><ref>Youtube video: {{Citation|last=Wil ho|title=Kaivosajo 2 4 2016|date=2016-04-03|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fXT_grEg8SA|accessdate=2018-03-02}}</ref>\n\n=== Public sporting events ===\nCallio Extreme Run was held 19.5.2018 with over 50 participants treading the whole 11 km from the main level at 1410 meters underground to the top via the main access tunnel. The mine tunnel network consists of hundreds of kilometers of tunnel, so for the safety of the participants all other intersections and pathways were cordoned off. Participants ranged from ultra-endurance athletes and triathlonists to regular exercisers. Adding to the challenge was the environmental conditions, as the run was constant uphill, the temperature over 23 \u00b0C and humidity varying between levels of 50%-100%. Runners all had to wear safety helmets fashioned with headlights. The men\u00b4s professional series was won by Tino Tiilikainen, a member of the Vuokatti SkiTeam, beating the previous record held by [[Sami Jauhoj\u00e4rvi|Sami]] [[Sami Jauhoj\u00e4rvi|Jauhoj\u00e4rvi]], with a time of 1:05:56. The womens professional series was won by Maija Oravam\u00e4ki with a time of 1:17:27.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.pyhajarvensanomat.fi/sivut/callio-extreme-runissa-huipputuloksia|title=Callio Extreme Runissa taas huipputuloksia|website=Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rven Sanomat|language=fi|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://my.raceresult.com/92824/results?lang=fi|title=my.race{{!}}result : : Callio Extreme Run, 19.05.2018|website=my.raceresult.com|language=fi|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref>\n\n[https://strongmancl.com/ Strongman Championships League] Callio World Record Breakers competition was organized by Callio at Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine on 7.9.2019. The competition was a part of the Strongman Champions League- circuit which has a total of 16 grand prix competition a year. The event was open to the public and televised as 12 strongmen from several countries participated in six events held on the mine mill grounds, as well as underground on the main level and in the open rock pit. 3 new world records were set in the farmerswalk, conan wheel, and deadlift categories by Aivars Smaukstelis, Antti Mouruj\u00e4rvi and Dainis Zageris.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://strongmancl.com/world-records/|title=Strongman Champions League / World Records|website=Strongman Champions League|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pyhajarvi.fi/fi/tapahtumakalenteri/strongman-champions-league-callio-world-record-breakers|title=Strongman Champions League Callio World Record Breakers|date=2019-08-16|website=Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rven kaupunki|language=fi|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref>\n\n=== Film productions ===\nCallio was also facilitating the use of Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine as a filming location for the new sci-fi television series The Whitewall, with a cast led by [[Aksel Hennie]], [[Vera Vitali]] and [[Eero Milonoff]]. It is a Finnish-Swedish collaboration between [[Yle]] and [[Sveriges Television|SVT]] that will premiere in 2020 and is the most expensive Finnish television series made, with a 900 000 euro budget per episode.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.keskipohjanmaa.fi/uutinen/553175|title=Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvelle suuren televisiosarjan kuvaukset \u2013 esitet\u00e4\u00e4n samaan aikaan Ruotsin ja Suomen televisiossa vuonna 2020|last=Savela|first=Antti|date=2018-10-29|website=KPK|language=fi|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref> The mine served as one location for filming, with sets both above and below ground, where a special film set was built 660 meters underground in abandoned storage tunnels. Filming in Pyh\u00e4salmi took place between November 2018 and April 2019 with a film crew of 50 people. Most of the extras required were locals and even miners themselves.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kaleva.fi/uutiset/kulttuuri/pyhajarven-kaivoksella-kuvataan-tv-sarjaa-700n-metrin-syvyydessa-tuottaja-tasta-tulee-erilainen-kuin-aiemmin-nahdyista-pohjoismaisista-sarjoista/813709/|title=Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rven kaivoksella kuvataan tv-sarjaa 700:n metrin syvyydess\u00e4 \u2013 Tuottaja: \"T\u00e4st\u00e4 tulee erilainen kuin aiemmin n\u00e4hdyist\u00e4 pohjoismaisista sarjoista\"|website=Kaleva.fi|language=fi|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://yle.fi/uutiset/3-10596674|title=Kalliin tieteissarjan kuvaukset py\u00f6riv\u00e4t Pyh\u00e4salmen kaivoksessa|website=Yle Uutiset|language=fi|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref>\n\nOther productions have also taken note of the unique location and in October 2019 the film Hiidenkirnu Giants Kettle will film scenes at the mine. The film is produced by Markku Hakala and is set in the 1970\u00b4s and is described as a mystical story about a woman, a man and a giant trapped in a barn.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.markkuhakala.com/giant.php|title=Hiidenkirnu|website=www.markkuhakala.com|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref>\n\n=== Recognitions ===\nCallio Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvi was awarded the [[Energy Globe Award|National Energy Globe Award]] Finland 2019 for its concept on pumped hydroelectrical energy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.energyglobe.info/finland2019?cl=en&id=331704|title=Energy Globe Award / national winner country sites|website=www.energyglobe.info|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref> The [[Energy Globe Award]] recognizes projects oriented in conservation of energy and utilization of renewable resources in 187 participating countries. The national winners will participate and compete for the World Energy Globe Award, with the ceremony taking place 12-13<sup>th</sup> November in Espoo, Finland to mark the awards 20<sup>th</sup> jubilee. The location was chosen as Espoo, because it was elected the most sustainable city in the world by United Nations in 2018. \n\n== Research projects ==\n\n=== Callio Lab ===\nOne major project Callio pioneered is the scientifically oriented [https://calliolab.com/ Callio Lab]. Callio Lab is a multidisciplinary R&D environment aiming to utilize better the unique infrastructure and facilities of the Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine. The underground environment has numerous possibilities for research and experimentation in fields of physics, geosciences, underground construction, microbiology, food production, and life sciences. Callio Lab aims to bring new users to the mine and facilitate the beginning of new projects. Open call is continuous and new experiments or research plans can be proposed on their website. Callio Lab\u00b4s workers assist new operators in getting started, this includes providing information, safety training and transportation in the mine as well as working as a liaison between them and the mine personnel. Callio Lab is a member of the [http://bsuin.eu/ BSUIN] network, which consists of underground laboratories and facilities in the [[Baltic region|Baltic region.]]<ref name=\":4\" /><ref name=\":9\" />\n\nCallio Lab's largest underground laboratory, Lab 2, was previously the prime candidate for the [[Large Apparatus studying Grand Unification and Neutrino Astrophysics|LAGUNA]] project, which fell through due to funding issues.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Nuijten|first=Guido Alexander|date=2011|title=LAGUNA DESIGN STUDY, Underground infrastructures and engineering|url=http://stacks.iop.org/1742-6596/308/i=1/a=012029|journal=Journal of Physics: Conference Series|language=en|volume=308|issue=1|pages=012029|doi=10.1088/1742-6596/308/1/012029|issn=1742-6596}}</ref><ref name=\":6\">{{Cite web|url=https://yle.fi/uutiset/3-7435750|title=Lagunan hiukkastutkimuspilotti yh\u00e4 l\u00e4hemp\u00e4n\u00e4 toteutumista|last=Ver\u00e4j\u00e4nkorva|first=Arto|date=August 27, 2014|website=Yle Uutiset|language=fi|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Buizza Avanzini|first=Margherita|date=24 March 2015|title=The LAGUNA-LBNO Project|journal=Physics Procedia|language=en|volume=61|pages=524\u2013533|doi=10.1016/j.phpro.2014.12.117|issn=1875-3892}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://yle.fi/uutiset/3-9413811|title=Toimittajalta: Tieteistarina Suomesta \u2013 Miksi miljardihanke luovutettiin Yhdysvaltoihin?|last=Ukkonen|first=Risto|date=July 7, 2017|website=Yle Uutiset|language=fi|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tiedetuubi.fi/videot/laguna-valtava-havaintonaite-kallion-sisalle|title=LAGUNA, valtava havaintonaite kallion sis\u00e4lle|last=M\u00e4kinen|first=Jari|date=|website=www.tiedetuubi.fi|language=fi|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref> LAGUNA is a proposed very large volume underground [[neutrino]] [[Neutrino observatory|observatory]], designed to study e.g., the excess of matter over [[antimatter]] in the universe. Pyh\u00e4salmi mine would have been at the optimal distance from the [[CERN]] particle accelerators, which would have provided the neutrino beams for the experiment.<ref name=\":7\" /><ref name=\":6\" />\n\n=== Callio Edible Insects from Mine ===\nCallio Edible Insects from Mine project is piloting underground insect production and is a two year project beginning in December 2018. It is a joint collaboration between the following entities: [[Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvi|city of Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvi]], Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine Oy, Entocube Oy, Probot Oy, M-Solutions Oy, Muon Solutions Oy and Callio Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvi. The aim is to build an ecological and efficient product plant.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://callio.info/natural-resources-business/edible-insects/|title=Edible insects|website=Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rven Callio - Maanalainen menestystekij\u00e4|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref> Principle characterisics of this type of production are remote control and -supervision and circular economy. Applications of technologies encompassing these characteristics can be found in subterranean living and space habitats. The tunnels of Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine bear a resemblance to the conditions of pressurized lava tunnels in Mars and as such provide a good environment to test out such innovations. The project will also compare the differences in production above ground and underground.  In July 2019 the first insect farm was built in lab 2 at 1430 meters underground. The first species grown there is house crickets ([[House cricket|Acheta domesticus]]) and the first generation has been successfully harvested. Due to the location of the farm, heating expenses are eliminated because the geothermal energy keeps the temperature at a constant 25 degrees. The crickets produced during the project cannot be sold because of legislation, but have been made into product samples.<ref name=\":10\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.talouselama.fi/uutiset/pyhasalmen-tyhjentyvassa-kaivoksessa-kasvatetaan-nyt-sirkkoja-maan-alla-testataan-ruokatuotantoa-joka-voisi-toimia-myos-marsin-laavatunneleissa/19cb54f8-1f8c-435e-a705-dbd3bd527f1e|title=Pyh\u00e4salmen tyhjentyv\u00e4ss\u00e4 kaivoksessa kasvatetaan nyt sirkkoja \u2013 maan alla testataan ruokatuotantoa, joka voisi toimia my\u00f6s Marsin laavatunneleissa|last=Palm\u00e9n|first=Joanna|website=Talousel\u00e4m\u00e4|language=fi|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://callio.info/2017/wp-content/uploads/CEIFM-pressijulkaisu-29.8_v2.pdf|title=Hy\u00f6nteistuotantoa Pyh\u00e4salmen kaivoksessa|last=|first=|date=29 August 2019|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n=== Plant Production in Mine ===\nPlant Production in Mine was a project and study conducted by the Natural Resources Institute of Finland (LUKE)[https://www.luke.fi/en/] in Callio Lab laboratories at 660 meters underground. The goal of the project was to study how plant production can be implemented in a controlled underground environment. The experiment began with growing common hop ([[Humulus lupulus]]) in April 2018 using hydroponic technology. Fertilization, watering, air ventilation and temperature was controlled through automation and remote control. If optimal growing conditions can be characterized, this would broach the possibility of year round production of hops with hundreds of harvests instead of just one. This could have the potential of replacing foreign imported hops for national breweries. Other plants that have been grown in the labs are potato, woad, and common nettle.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kaleva.fi/uutiset/pohjois-suomi/humala-kasvaa-pyhasalmen-kaivoksessa-660-metrin-syvyydessa-maan-alla-vuodenajalla-tai-vuorokaudenajalla-ei-ole-valia/805529/|title=Humala kasvaa Pyh\u00e4salmen kaivoksessa 660 metrin syvyydess\u00e4 \u2013 maan alla vuodenajalla tai vuorokaudenajalla ei ole v\u00e4li\u00e4|website=Kaleva.fi|language=fi|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref><ref name=\":5\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.kaleva.fi/uutiset/galleriat/pyhasalmen-kaivoksessa-kasvatetaan-nokkosta-ja-perunaa/10269/|title=Kuvagalleria: Pyh\u00e4salmen kaivoksessa kasvatetaan nokkosta ja perunaa|last=Kontiainen|first=Jarmo|date=July 7, 2017|website=Kaleva.fi|language=fi|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref>\n\n=== Intelligent Lighting ===\nThe Intelligent Lighting pilot study conducted at Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine is studying the effects of artificial light in an underground working environment. The main area of study is the facilities at the main level, particularly the office spaces. The environment is naturally devoid of natural light and the lighting is constant 24/7. How this affects the workers physiologically and psychologically was studied through physiological measurements and interviews. In October 2019 the office spaces were fitted with intelligent adaptive lighting programmed to each user\u2019s individual needs. This will be followed by a study period to see whether these intelligent lighting solutions based on architectural lighting principles promote the employees well-being.The study is conducted by researchers from the [[University of Oulu]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://jultika.oulu.fi/Record/nbnfioulu-201905292233|title=Lighting at the end of the tunnel : the design of adaptive and intelligent lighting for an underground workspace|last=Pujol Moll\u00e0|first=Mireia|date=2019|website=jultika.oulu.fi|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oulu.fi/ksi-eng/node/60781|title=Innovative light for innovative spaces|website=www.oulu.fi|language=en|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref>\n\n=== MINETRAIN ===\nThe [http://minetrain.eu/contact.html MINETRAIN] project is coordinated by the Oulu Mining School and aims to create a thorough training program for professionals in the mining industry. At the same time experience is gained from whether a mine heading toward closure could be transformed into a state of the art training center. The approach of the program is holistic, providing attendees with training spanning the whole life cycle of a mine. The Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine is especially well equipped for this, because it encompasses all aspects of mining from excavation to mill processing. The program provides lectures as well as hands on learning opportunities and can be tailored to suit the participants previous experience. The project is funded by [https://eitrawmaterials.eu/ EIT Raw Materials]. The first course was held in August 2019 with a class of 15 international professionals. The project leaders believe that through immersive training programs such as these, future mining operations can become more efficient and sustainable. They help the industry gain more knowledge and adopt a holistic point of view towards production and planning.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://minetrain.eu/|title=MINETRAIN|website=minetrain.eu|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref>\n\n=== Energy Mine ===\nThe EAKR funded project Energy Mine began in February 2017 and will run until 2020. It is studying what the geothermal energy potential of Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine is and whether it can be harnessed in a financially profitable way. The project aims to ascertain what technologies and applications could be applied in this field of study both from a scientific and economic point of view. Other supporters of this project include Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine and the city of Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvi.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://calliolab.com/research/projects/|title=Projects|website=Callio Lab - a world class underground center located in Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvi, Finland|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.microentre.fi/hankkeet/energiakaivos/|title=Energiakaivos|website=MicroEntre- Luotettava asiantuntija yritt\u00e4j\u00e4\u00e4 l\u00e4hell\u00e4.|language=fi|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref>\n\n=== Underground Rescue ===\nCallio is hosting the Callio Underground Rescue- project. The Pyh\u00e4salmi mine will be the site of Finland\u2019s first underground fire-, rescue- and safety training center. The project secured funding for 2019 through 2022 and the projected cost is 739000 euros. 70% of this came from the EAKR fund. As of now, the closest training center of this type is in Norway.  The project aims to utilize the soon to be closed mine and it\u2019s already existing facilities and infrastructure. The main coordinator is the city of Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvi with numerous professional partners and businesses, that specialize in fire extinction and safety systems, ICT solutions, and tunnel- and shaft rescue operations. These partners include Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine Oy, Agnico Eagle Finland Oy, Sotkamo Silver AB, Anglo American Sakatti Mining Oy, J&T Technology Oy, M-Solutions Oy and Posiva Oy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://callio.info/2017/wp-content/uploads/Tiedote-25.6.2019.pdf|title=Underground Rescue|last=|first=|date=25 June 2019|website=Mine for Business - Callio|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n=== Pumped Hydroelectric Storage Facility ===\nIt was announced on December 4<sup>th</sup>, 2019 that Pumped Hydro Storage Sweden AB and Callio have signed a co-operation agreement to build a demo model of a [[Pumped-storage hydroelectricity|pumped hydroelectric energy]] storage facility in the Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine. The purpose of this co-operation is to design and develop on a smaller scale a pilot facility which can later be implemented in a full-scale version. Work is already underway, including the technical plans, timetables, and financing of the project.\n\nThis is the first phase of Callio's plans for a pumped hydroelectric storage facility in Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine. Once the creation, testing and optimizing it this demo facility for use is completed, Callio will move to phase two. Phase two aims to negotiate the fulfillment of a full-scale 75MW facility.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businessoulu.com/fi/uutiset/pumppuvesivoimaan-perustuvan-energiavaraston-demolaitos-toteutumassa-pyhajarven-callioon.html|title=Pumppuvesivoimaan perustuvan energiavaraston demolaitos toteutumassa Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rven Callioon|website=www.businessoulu.com|language=FI|access-date=2020-01-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ostologistiikka.fi/kategoriat/teknologia/pyhajarven-pumppuvesivoiman-demolaitos-tekeille|title=Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rven pumppuvesivoiman demolaitos tekeille - Osto&Logistiikka|website=www.ostologistiikka.fi|language=fi|access-date=2020-01-10}}</ref>\n\n== The Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine ==\n\nThe overall depth of the Pyh\u00e4salmi mine is 1450&nbsp;m (4760&nbsp;ft), making it the deepest base metal mine in Europe.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.first-quantum.com/Our-Business/operating-mines/Pyhasalmi/default.aspx|title=Pyh\u00e4salmi Copper mine|last=|first=|date=|website=www.first-quantum.com|language=en-CA|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.euronews.com/2012/05/02/new-life-for-old-metal-mines|title=New life for old metal mines|date=2012-05-02|work=euronews|access-date=2018-03-02|language=en}}</ref> Its main metals are [[copper]] and [[Zinc (element)|zinc]].\n\nThe mine was opened in 1962 by [[Outokumpu]], sold to [[Inmet Mining|Inmet mining]] in 2002, and obtained by [[First Quantum Minerals]] in 2013.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.kaleva.fi/uutiset/pohjois-suomi/pyhasalmen-kaivoksella-haikea-tunnelma/123595/|title=Pyh\u00e4salmen kaivoksella haikea tunnelma|date=December 20, 2001|work=Kaleva.fi|access-date=2018-03-02|language=fi}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://yle.fi/uutiset/3-6551819|title=Kanadalainen kuparij\u00e4tti ostaa my\u00f6s Suomessa toimivan kaivosyhti\u00f6n|last=Harala|first=Samuli|date=March 24, 2013|website=Yle Uutiset|language=fi|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref> The mine was previously planned to close by the end of 2019, but has been granted approximately 14 months more of mining activity due to an increase in demand for [[pyrite]] from [[Yara International|Yara]] in Siilinj\u00e4rvi. Pyrite is a by product of copper and zinc mining. As of now, mining is going to be continued until spring 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://yle.fi/uutiset/3-10888381|title=Pyh\u00e4salmen kaivos sai yli vuoden jatkoajan lannoitetehtaan ansiosta|website=Yle Uutiset|language=fi|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref> Above-ground refinery will continue until 2025.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.kauppalehti.fi/uutiset/yara-ja-pyhasalmen-kaivos-pitkaaikaiseen-sopimukseen-pyriittitoimituksista/fziHDRG6|title=Yara ja Pyh\u00e4salmen kaivos pitk\u00e4aikaiseen sopimukseen pyriittitoimituksista {{!}} Kauppalehti|last=M\u00e4h\u00f6nen|first=Erno|date=August 9, 2016|website=Kauppalehti|language=fi-FI|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref>\n\nThe mine safety has improved significantly over the last decades, and the underground mine has become a test bed for new (often award-winning<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.tekniikkatalous.fi/tekniikka/metalli/2003-09-09/Malminrikastus-sai-automaatiopalkinnon-3267123.html|title=Malminrikastus sai automaatiopalkinnon|date=September 9, 2003|work=Tekniikka & Talous|access-date=2018-03-02|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.tekniikkatalous.fi/arkisto/2006-01-26/Kaivosj%C3%A4rjestelm%C3%A4-sai-automaatiopalkinnon-3282535.html|title=Kaivosj\u00e4rjestelm\u00e4 sai automaatiopalkinnon|date=January 26, 2006|work=Tekniikka & Talous|access-date=2018-03-02|language=en}}</ref>) access control, monitoring and automation technology.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rfidjournal.com/articles/view?12925|title=Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine Will Expand RFID System to Boost Safety|last=Claire Swedberg and Mark Roberti|date=April 8, 2015|website=www.rfidjournal.com|language=en|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/indoor-smartphone-compass-locater|title=Finnish startup can locate you indoors using magnetic field anomalies|last=Clark|first=Liat|date=April 8, 2015|work=Wired Magazine|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.tekniikkatalous.fi/tekniikka/ict/2015-06-01/Ericsson-kokeilee-5G-verkkoja-kaivoksessa---Malmirekka-et%C3%A4ohjaukseen-3321894.html|title=Ericsson kokeilee 5G-verkkoja kaivoksessa - Malmirekka et\u00e4ohjaukseen|last=Ikkala|first=Tapio|date=June 1, 2015|work=Tekniikka & Talous|access-date=2018-03-02|language=en}}</ref> Underground accidents in Pyh\u00e4salmi are very rare, and the last fatality occurred in 1995.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hs.fi/kotimaa/art-2000003446972.html|title=Mies kuoli pudottuaan 60 metri\u00e4 kaivoksessa Pyh\u00e4salmella|last=Marttinen|first=Heikki|date=1995-07-03|work=Helsingin Sanomat|access-date=2018-03-02|language=fi-FI}}</ref> Several easily contained on-ground refinery fires have however occurred at the site during the 2000s.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hs.fi/kotimaa/art-2000004090027.html|title=Palo Pyh\u00e4salmen kaivoksella|date=2002-10-14|work=Helsingin Sanomat|access-date=2018-03-02|language=fi-FI}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.kaleva.fi/uutiset/pohjois-suomi/kaivoksessa-tulipalo/83355/|title=Kaivoksessa tulipalo|date=May 18, 2006|work=Kaleva.fi|access-date=2018-03-02|language=fi}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.kaleva.fi/uutiset/kotimaa/kaivospaloa-sammutettiin-30-metrin-korkeudella-pyhajarvella/169981/|title=Kaivospaloa sammutettiin 30 metrin korkeudella Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvell\u00e4|date=May 22, 2010|work=Kaleva.fi|access-date=2018-03-02|language=fi}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.kaleva.fi/uutiset/kotimaa/pyhasalmen-kaivoksen-tornissa-paloi-sammutustyot-70-metrin-korkeudessa/690837/|title=Pyh\u00e4salmen kaivoksen tornissa paloi - sammutusty\u00f6t 70 metrin korkeudessa|date=March 1, 2015|work=Kaleva.fi|access-date=2018-03-02|language=fi}}</ref> In 2012, explosives contaminated with pyrite ore were sent from the Pyh\u00e4salmi mine for destruction at the Forcit ammunition factory in [[Vihtavuori]], where (after a year in storage) the container started to heat up and smoke.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://yle.fi/uutiset/3-6917325|title=Tukes: Varomattomuus aiheutti Vihtavuoren suuronnettomuusvaaran|last=Pajunen|first=Ilpo|date=November 5, 2013|website=Yle Uutiset|language=fi|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.is.fi/kotimaa/art-2000000677454.html|title=Vihtavuoren onnettomuustutkinnan tulokset julki - t\u00e4m\u00e4 aiheutti suuronnettomuuden vaaran|date=2013-11-05|work=Ilta-Sanomat|access-date=2018-03-02|language=fi-FI}}</ref> The reason for this potentially dangerous situation was revealed to be careless handling and packaging at the mine. This prompted significant changes in the safety protocols, and since 2013 all hazardous waste is destroyed on-site in Pyh\u00e4salmi.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://yle.fi/uutiset/3-6746708|title=Laukaan vaaratilanne johti muutoksiin Pyh\u00e4salmen kaivoksella|last=Karppinen|first=Kirsi|date=July 25, 2013|website=Yle Uutiset|language=fi|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref>\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://callio.info/ Callio website]\n* [https://calliolab.com/ CallioLab website]\n* [https://sketchfab.com/models/689513c4b34f4246ba0b84f5744153a5 3D video of the Callio facilities] at [[Sketchfab]]\n* [http://bsuin.eu/ BSUIN (Baltic Sea Underground Facilities and Innovation Network) website]\n*[http://minetrain.eu/contact.html MINETRAIN] \n\n== References ==\n<!-- Inline citations added to your article will automatically display here. See https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WP:REFB for instructions on how to add citations. -->\n{{reflist}}\n*\n{{Underground laboratories}}\n\n[[Category:Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvi]]\n[[Category:Particle physics facilities]]\n[[Category:Underground laboratories]]\n[[Category:Laboratories in Finland]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|name=Callio Pyh\u00e4salmi\n|coordinates={{coord|63.659902|N|26.041062|E|display=inline,title}}\n|pushpin_map=Finland\n|pushpin_map_caption=Location in [[Northern Ostrobothnia]] in [[Finland]]\n|image_skyline=Pyhasalmi_mine_old_tower_and_surroundings.jpg\n|image_caption=Old tower and surrounding buildings of Pyh\u00e4salmi mine\n}}\n\n'''Callio''' is a project to oversee the reuse of the [[Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine]], located in the [[Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvi|town of Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvi]] in [[Finland]]. Callio aims to make Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine an operating environment for businesses and an [[underground facility|underground research facility]].\n\nCallio is a joint project by the town of Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvi and the [[University of Oulu]]. In 2017 the facility joined the \"Baltic Sea Underground Facilities and Innovation Network\" ([http://bsuin.eu/ BSUIN]).<ref name=\":9\">{{Cite news|url=https://projects.interreg-baltic.eu/projects/bsuin-102.html|title=BSUIN|work=Interreg Baltic Sea Region \u2013 Project Library|access-date=2018-03-02|language=de}}</ref><ref name=\":3\">{{Cite news|url=https://calliolab.com/underground-laboratories-platforms-innovation-new-businesses-international-research-group-meeting-pyhajarvi-finland/|title=Underground Laboratories|date=2017-09-26|work=Callio Lab|access-date=2018-03-02|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.kaleva.fi/uutiset/pohjois-suomi/pyhajarvi-paasi-mukaan-kaivosyhteistyohon-jossa-kehitetaan-maanalaisia-laboratorioita/771611/|title=Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvi p\u00e4\u00e4si mukaan kaivosyhteisty\u00f6h\u00f6n, jossa kehitet\u00e4\u00e4n maanalaisia laboratorioita|last=Rahko|first=Pekka|date=September 26, 2017|work=Kaleva.fi|access-date=2018-03-02|language=fi}}</ref>\n\nThe word \u201dcallio\u201d is an [[Anglicisation|anglicised]] version of the Finnish word \u201dkallio\u201d [kael-lee-oh], meaning crystalline [[bedrock]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/kallio|title=kallio - Wiktionary|website=en.wiktionary.org|language=en|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kielitoimistonsanakirja.fi/kallio|title=kallio - Kielitoimiston sanakirja|last=|first=|date=|website=www.kielitoimistonsanakirja.fi|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://webxicon.org/search.php?id=91951|title=kallio from Finnish to all languages|last=|first=|date=|website=webxicon.org|language=en|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref>\n\n== Facilities and access ==\nCallio is an umbrella organization for a variety of non-mining activities in and around the mine. Of these, '''Callio Lab'''<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://calliolab.com/|title=Callio Lab|last=|first=|date=|website=Callio Lab|language=en-US|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref> oversees scientific research and development. Proposed new activities include a secure underground [[data center]], pumped hydroelectrical [[Pumped-storage hydroelectricity|energy storage]], plant and fungus growing laboratories, breeding sites for insects and fish, and several other types of underground businesses.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.iltalehti.fi/kotimaa/201801302200704544_u0.shtml|title=Euroopan syvin kaivos lopettaa Pyh\u00e4salmella|last=Jokinen|first=Juha Veli|date=January 29, 2018|work=Ilta-Sanomat|access-date=2018-03-02|language=fi-FI}}</ref><ref name=\":8\">{{Cite web|url=http://callio.info/|title=Callio|last=|first=|date=|website=Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rven Callio|language=en-US|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref>\n\nAs of 2018,<ref name=\":3\" /><ref name=\":4\" /> there are four environmentally controlled laboratories in Callio. Listed top-to-bottom, they are:\n* Lab 1 at 75 m level (245&nbsp;ft depth), occupied by the EMMA experiment;\n* Lab 4 at 660&nbsp;m (2165&nbsp;ft);\n* Lab 3 at 990&nbsp;m (3250&nbsp;ft);\n* Lab 2 at 1430&nbsp;m (4690&nbsp;ft), 120 m<sup>2</sup>, height \u22489 m, currently occupied by the Callio Edible Insects from Mine project<ref name=\":10\" />.\n* Numerous additional service, storage and maintenance halls exist along the access tunnel. \nThe ambient temperature within the mine depends on the depth but is otherwise constant. At the Lab 4 (660 m) level it is 15&nbsp;\u00b0C (59&nbsp;\u00b0F) and at Lab 2 (1430 m) level 28&nbsp;\u00b0C (82&nbsp;\u00b0F).<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=https://yle.fi/uutiset/3-9971777|title=Suomalaisen kaivoksen tunneleissa 660 metrin syvyydess\u00e4 kasvaa perunaa \u2013 \"T\u00e4m\u00e4 mullistaa ruoantuotantoa maailmalla\"|last=Juopperi|first=Hanna|date=December 15, 2017|website=Yle Uutiset|language=fi|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref>\n[[File:Emma koe.JPG|thumb|Measurement station of [[Centre for Underground Physics in Pyh\u00e4salmi|EMMA]], one of the longest-standing experiments in the Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine.]]\nCurrently (2018) the mine harbors two scientific experiments: [[Centre for Underground Physics in Pyh\u00e4salmi|C14 liquid scintillator]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://callio.info/callio-lab/c14-experiment/|title=C14 Experiment|work=Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rven Callio|access-date=2018-03-02|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=\":7\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.nupecc.org/presentations/engvist_jun14.pdf|title=Astroparticle Physics in the Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine|last=Enqvist|first=Timo|date=June 13, 2014|website=www.nupecc.org|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref> and [[Centre for Underground Physics in Pyh\u00e4salmi|EMMA]],<ref name=\":7\" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://callio.info/callio-lab/emma-experiment/|title=EMMA experiment|work=Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rven Callio|access-date=2018-03-02|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.symmetrymagazine.org/article/1000-meters-below|title=1,000 meters below|last=Shivni|first=Rashmi|date=May 31, 2016|work=symmetry magazine|access-date=2018-03-02|language=en}}</ref> operated by [[Centre for Underground Physics in Pyh\u00e4salmi|CUPP]], [[University of Oulu]] and [[University of Jyv\u00e4skyl\u00e4]].\n\n=== Access ===\nThe \"main level\" of the mine is at 1400 meters depth, and is equipped with service and social facilities, e.g., a restaurant and the deepest sauna in the world.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://diepresse.com/home/leben/reise/5201433/FinnlandSauna_Hitze-Bier-und-Birkenzweige|title=Finnland-Sauna: Hitze, Bier und Birkenzweige|last=Knoller|first=Rasso|date=April 18, 2017|work=Die Presse|access-date=2018-03-02|language=de}}</ref> Accessing the main level from the surface takes just 3 minutes using the elevator (average speed 8&nbsp;m/s, maximum 12&nbsp;m/s).<ref name=\":4\" /> The same descent takes about 30 minutes by car, along the 11&nbsp;km long decline access tunnel.<ref name=\":8\" />\n\n== Activities ==\nRecently the mine has opened up for a variety of cultural activities. It has hosted the deepest concert in the world (by [[Agonizer]] at 1271 m ) as well as dance performances.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/world-records/deepest-concert-underground|title=Deepest concert underground|date=August 4, 2007|work=Guinness World Records|access-date=2018-03-02|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://kp24.fi/uutiset/310558/tanssi-tila-ja-luonto-yhdistyvat-laguna-lahempana-sydanta|title=Tanssi, tila ja luonto yhdistyv\u00e4t: Laguna - L\u00e4hemp\u00e4n\u00e4 syd\u00e4nt\u00e4|date=July 24, 2012|work=KP24|access-date=2018-03-02|language=fi-FI}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.liikekieli.com/archives/4647|title=Kuvia Petri Kekonin Lagunasta T\u00e4ydenkuun tansseilta|last=Lamberg|first=Veera|date=August 7, 2012|work=Liikekieli.com|access-date=2018-03-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160417100528/http://www.liikekieli.com/archives/4647|archive-date=April 17, 2016|url-status=dead|language=fi}}</ref> The 11&nbsp;km long spiral-shaped main tunnel has also seen several uphill running and cycling competitions.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://hikisetsiivut.blogspot.fi/2013/11/pyhajarven-alto-de-langliru.html|title=Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rven Alto de L'Angliru|last=Ovaska|first=Kimmo|date=November 3, 2013|website=hikisetsiivut.blogspot.fi|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref><ref>Youtube video: {{Citation|last=Pohti SkiTeam|title=Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvi Tour Trailer mp4|date=2016-08-16|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EpONbrTo77E|accessdate=2018-03-02}}</ref><ref>Youtube video: {{Citation|last=Wil ho|title=Kaivosajo 2 4 2016|date=2016-04-03|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fXT_grEg8SA|accessdate=2018-03-02}}</ref>\n\n=== Public sporting events ===\nCallio Extreme Run was held 19.5.2018 with over 50 participants treading the whole 11 km from the main level at 1410 meters underground to the top via the main access tunnel. The mine tunnel network consists of hundreds of kilometers of tunnel, so for the safety of the participants all other intersections and pathways were cordoned off. Participants ranged from ultra-endurance athletes and triathlonists to regular exercisers. Adding to the challenge was the environmental conditions, as the run was constant uphill, the temperature over 23 \u00b0C and humidity varying between levels of 50%-100%. Runners all had to wear safety helmets fashioned with headlights. The men\u00b4s professional series was won by Tino Tiilikainen, a member of the Vuokatti SkiTeam, beating the previous record held by [[Sami Jauhoj\u00e4rvi|Sami]] [[Sami Jauhoj\u00e4rvi|Jauhoj\u00e4rvi]], with a time of 1:05:56. The womens professional series was won by Maija Oravam\u00e4ki with a time of 1:17:27.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.pyhajarvensanomat.fi/sivut/callio-extreme-runissa-huipputuloksia|title=Callio Extreme Runissa taas huipputuloksia|website=Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rven Sanomat|language=fi|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://my.raceresult.com/92824/results?lang=fi|title=my.race{{!}}result : : Callio Extreme Run, 19.05.2018|website=my.raceresult.com|language=fi|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref>\n\n[https://strongmancl.com/ Strongman Championships League] Callio World Record Breakers competition was organized by Callio at Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine on 7.9.2019. The competition was a part of the Strongman Champions League- circuit which has a total of 16 grand prix competition a year. The event was open to the public and televised as 12 strongmen from several countries participated in six events held on the mine mill grounds, as well as underground on the main level and in the open rock pit. 3 new world records were set in the farmerswalk, conan wheel, and deadlift categories by Aivars Smaukstelis, Antti Mouruj\u00e4rvi and Dainis Zageris.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://strongmancl.com/world-records/|title=Strongman Champions League / World Records|website=Strongman Champions League|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pyhajarvi.fi/fi/tapahtumakalenteri/strongman-champions-league-callio-world-record-breakers|title=Strongman Champions League Callio World Record Breakers|date=2019-08-16|website=Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rven kaupunki|language=fi|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref>\n\n=== Film productions ===\nCallio was also facilitating the use of Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine as a filming location for the new sci-fi television series The Whitewall, with a cast led by [[Aksel Hennie]], [[Vera Vitali]] and [[Eero Milonoff]]. It is a Finnish-Swedish collaboration between [[Yle]] and [[Sveriges Television|SVT]] that will premiere in 2020 and is the most expensive Finnish television series made, with a 900 000 euro budget per episode.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.keskipohjanmaa.fi/uutinen/553175|title=Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvelle suuren televisiosarjan kuvaukset \u2013 esitet\u00e4\u00e4n samaan aikaan Ruotsin ja Suomen televisiossa vuonna 2020|last=Savela|first=Antti|date=2018-10-29|website=KPK|language=fi|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref> The mine served as one location for filming, with sets both above and below ground, where a special film set was built 660 meters underground in abandoned storage tunnels. Filming in Pyh\u00e4salmi took place between November 2018 and April 2019 with a film crew of 50 people. Most of the extras required were locals and even miners themselves.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kaleva.fi/uutiset/kulttuuri/pyhajarven-kaivoksella-kuvataan-tv-sarjaa-700n-metrin-syvyydessa-tuottaja-tasta-tulee-erilainen-kuin-aiemmin-nahdyista-pohjoismaisista-sarjoista/813709/|title=Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rven kaivoksella kuvataan tv-sarjaa 700:n metrin syvyydess\u00e4 \u2013 Tuottaja: \"T\u00e4st\u00e4 tulee erilainen kuin aiemmin n\u00e4hdyist\u00e4 pohjoismaisista sarjoista\"|website=Kaleva.fi|language=fi|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://yle.fi/uutiset/3-10596674|title=Kalliin tieteissarjan kuvaukset py\u00f6riv\u00e4t Pyh\u00e4salmen kaivoksessa|website=Yle Uutiset|language=fi|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref>\n\nOther productions have also taken note of the unique location and in October 2019 the film Hiidenkirnu Giants Kettle will film scenes at the mine. The film is produced by Markku Hakala and is set in the 1970\u00b4s and is described as a mystical story about a woman, a man and a giant trapped in a barn.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.markkuhakala.com/giant.php|title=Hiidenkirnu|website=www.markkuhakala.com|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref>\n\n=== Recognitions ===\nCallio Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvi was awarded the [[Energy Globe Award|National Energy Globe Award]] Finland 2019 for its concept on pumped hydroelectrical energy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.energyglobe.info/finland2019?cl=en&id=331704|title=Energy Globe Award / national winner country sites|website=www.energyglobe.info|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref> The [[Energy Globe Award]] recognizes projects oriented in conservation of energy and utilization of renewable resources in 187 participating countries. The national winners will participate and compete for the World Energy Globe Award, with the ceremony taking place 12-13<sup>th</sup> November in Espoo, Finland to mark the awards 20<sup>th</sup> jubilee. The location was chosen as Espoo, because it was elected the most sustainable city in the world by United Nations in 2018. \n\n== Research projects ==\n\n=== Callio Lab ===\nOne major project Callio pioneered is the scientifically oriented [https://calliolab.com/ Callio Lab]. Callio Lab is a multidisciplinary R&D environment aiming to utilize better the unique infrastructure and facilities of the Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine. The underground environment has numerous possibilities for research and experimentation in fields of physics, geosciences, underground construction, microbiology, food production, and life sciences. Callio Lab aims to bring new users to the mine and facilitate the beginning of new projects. Open call is continuous and new experiments or research plans can be proposed on their website. Callio Lab\u00b4s workers assist new operators in getting started, this includes providing information, safety training and transportation in the mine as well as working as a liaison between them and the mine personnel. Callio Lab is a member of the [http://bsuin.eu/ BSUIN] network, which consists of underground laboratories and facilities in the [[Baltic region|Baltic region.]]<ref name=\":4\" /><ref name=\":9\" />\n\nCallio Lab's largest underground laboratory, Lab 2, was previously the prime candidate for the [[Large Apparatus studying Grand Unification and Neutrino Astrophysics|LAGUNA]] project, which fell through due to funding issues.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Nuijten|first=Guido Alexander|date=2011|title=LAGUNA DESIGN STUDY, Underground infrastructures and engineering|url=http://stacks.iop.org/1742-6596/308/i=1/a=012029|journal=Journal of Physics: Conference Series|language=en|volume=308|issue=1|pages=012029|doi=10.1088/1742-6596/308/1/012029|issn=1742-6596}}</ref><ref name=\":6\">{{Cite web|url=https://yle.fi/uutiset/3-7435750|title=Lagunan hiukkastutkimuspilotti yh\u00e4 l\u00e4hemp\u00e4n\u00e4 toteutumista|last=Ver\u00e4j\u00e4nkorva|first=Arto|date=August 27, 2014|website=Yle Uutiset|language=fi|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Buizza Avanzini|first=Margherita|date=24 March 2015|title=The LAGUNA-LBNO Project|journal=Physics Procedia|language=en|volume=61|pages=524\u2013533|doi=10.1016/j.phpro.2014.12.117|issn=1875-3892}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://yle.fi/uutiset/3-9413811|title=Toimittajalta: Tieteistarina Suomesta \u2013 Miksi miljardihanke luovutettiin Yhdysvaltoihin?|last=Ukkonen|first=Risto|date=July 7, 2017|website=Yle Uutiset|language=fi|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tiedetuubi.fi/videot/laguna-valtava-havaintonaite-kallion-sisalle|title=LAGUNA, valtava havaintonaite kallion sis\u00e4lle|last=M\u00e4kinen|first=Jari|date=|website=www.tiedetuubi.fi|language=fi|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref> LAGUNA is a proposed very large volume underground [[neutrino]] [[Neutrino observatory|observatory]], designed to study e.g., the excess of matter over [[antimatter]] in the universe. Pyh\u00e4salmi mine would have been at the optimal distance from the [[CERN]] particle accelerators, which would have provided the neutrino beams for the experiment.<ref name=\":7\" /><ref name=\":6\" />\n\n=== Callio Edible Insects from Mine ===\nCallio Edible Insects from Mine project is piloting underground insect production and is a two year project beginning in December 2018. It is a joint collaboration between the following entities: [[Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvi|city of Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvi]], Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine Oy, Entocube Oy, Probot Oy, M-Solutions Oy, Muon Solutions Oy and Callio Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvi. The aim is to build an ecological and efficient product plant.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://callio.info/natural-resources-business/edible-insects/|title=Edible insects|website=Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rven Callio - Maanalainen menestystekij\u00e4|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref> Principle characterisics of this type of production are remote control and -supervision and circular economy. Applications of technologies encompassing these characteristics can be found in subterranean living and space habitats. The tunnels of Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine bear a resemblance to the conditions of pressurized lava tunnels in Mars and as such provide a good environment to test out such innovations. The project will also compare the differences in production above ground and underground.  In July 2019 the first insect farm was built in lab 2 at 1430 meters underground. The first species grown there is house crickets ([[House cricket|Acheta domesticus]]) and the first generation has been successfully harvested. Due to the location of the farm, heating expenses are eliminated because the geothermal energy keeps the temperature at a constant 25 degrees. The crickets produced during the project cannot be sold because of legislation, but have been made into product samples.<ref name=\":10\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.talouselama.fi/uutiset/pyhasalmen-tyhjentyvassa-kaivoksessa-kasvatetaan-nyt-sirkkoja-maan-alla-testataan-ruokatuotantoa-joka-voisi-toimia-myos-marsin-laavatunneleissa/19cb54f8-1f8c-435e-a705-dbd3bd527f1e|title=Pyh\u00e4salmen tyhjentyv\u00e4ss\u00e4 kaivoksessa kasvatetaan nyt sirkkoja \u2013 maan alla testataan ruokatuotantoa, joka voisi toimia my\u00f6s Marsin laavatunneleissa|last=Palm\u00e9n|first=Joanna|website=Talousel\u00e4m\u00e4|language=fi|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://callio.info/2017/wp-content/uploads/CEIFM-pressijulkaisu-29.8_v2.pdf|title=Hy\u00f6nteistuotantoa Pyh\u00e4salmen kaivoksessa|last=|first=|date=29 August 2019|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n=== Plant Production in Mine ===\nPlant Production in Mine was a project and study conducted by the Natural Resources Institute of Finland (LUKE)[https://www.luke.fi/en/] in Callio Lab laboratories at 660 meters underground. The goal of the project was to study how plant production can be implemented in a controlled underground environment. The experiment began with growing common hop ([[Humulus lupulus]]) in April 2018 using hydroponic technology. Fertilization, watering, air ventilation and temperature was controlled through automation and remote control. If optimal growing conditions can be characterized, this would broach the possibility of year round production of hops with hundreds of harvests instead of just one. This could have the potential of replacing foreign imported hops for national breweries. Other plants that have been grown in the labs are potato, woad, and common nettle.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kaleva.fi/uutiset/pohjois-suomi/humala-kasvaa-pyhasalmen-kaivoksessa-660-metrin-syvyydessa-maan-alla-vuodenajalla-tai-vuorokaudenajalla-ei-ole-valia/805529/|title=Humala kasvaa Pyh\u00e4salmen kaivoksessa 660 metrin syvyydess\u00e4 \u2013 maan alla vuodenajalla tai vuorokaudenajalla ei ole v\u00e4li\u00e4|website=Kaleva.fi|language=fi|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref><ref name=\":5\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.kaleva.fi/uutiset/galleriat/pyhasalmen-kaivoksessa-kasvatetaan-nokkosta-ja-perunaa/10269/|title=Kuvagalleria: Pyh\u00e4salmen kaivoksessa kasvatetaan nokkosta ja perunaa|last=Kontiainen|first=Jarmo|date=July 7, 2017|website=Kaleva.fi|language=fi|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref>\n\n=== Intelligent Lighting ===\nThe Intelligent Lighting pilot study conducted at Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine is studying the effects of artificial light in an underground working environment. The main area of study is the facilities at the main level, particularly the office spaces. The environment is naturally devoid of natural light and the lighting is constant 24/7. How this affects the workers physiologically and psychologically was studied through physiological measurements and interviews. In October 2019 the office spaces were fitted with intelligent adaptive lighting programmed to each user\u2019s individual needs. This will be followed by a study period to see whether these intelligent lighting solutions based on architectural lighting principles promote the employees well-being.The study is conducted by researchers from the [[University of Oulu]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://jultika.oulu.fi/Record/nbnfioulu-201905292233|title=Lighting at the end of the tunnel : the design of adaptive and intelligent lighting for an underground workspace|last=Pujol Moll\u00e0|first=Mireia|date=2019|website=jultika.oulu.fi|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oulu.fi/ksi-eng/node/60781|title=Innovative light for innovative spaces|website=www.oulu.fi|language=en|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref>\n\n=== MINETRAIN ===\nThe [http://minetrain.eu/contact.html MINETRAIN] project is coordinated by the Oulu Mining School and aims to create a thorough training program for professionals in the mining industry. At the same time experience is gained from whether a mine heading toward closure could be transformed into a state of the art training center. The approach of the program is holistic, providing attendees with training spanning the whole life cycle of a mine. The Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine is especially well equipped for this, because it encompasses all aspects of mining from excavation to mill processing. The program provides lectures as well as hands on learning opportunities and can be tailored to suit the participants previous experience. The project is funded by [https://eitrawmaterials.eu/ EIT Raw Materials]. The first course was held in August 2019 with a class of 15 international professionals. The project leaders believe that through immersive training programs such as these, future mining operations can become more efficient and sustainable. They help the industry gain more knowledge and adopt a holistic point of view towards production and planning.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://minetrain.eu/|title=MINETRAIN|website=minetrain.eu|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref>\n\n=== Energy Mine ===\nThe EAKR funded project Energy Mine began in February 2017 and will run until 2020. It is studying what the geothermal energy potential of Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine is and whether it can be harnessed in a financially profitable way. The project aims to ascertain what technologies and applications could be applied in this field of study both from a scientific and economic point of view. Other supporters of this project include Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine and the city of Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvi.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://calliolab.com/research/projects/|title=Projects|website=Callio Lab - a world class underground center located in Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvi, Finland|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.microentre.fi/hankkeet/energiakaivos/|title=Energiakaivos|website=MicroEntre- Luotettava asiantuntija yritt\u00e4j\u00e4\u00e4 l\u00e4hell\u00e4.|language=fi|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref>\n\n=== Underground Rescue ===\nCallio is hosting the Callio Underground Rescue- project. The Pyh\u00e4salmi mine will be the site of Finland\u2019s first underground fire-, rescue- and safety training center. The project secured funding for 2019 through 2022 and the projected cost is 739000 euros. 70% of this came from the EAKR fund. As of now, the closest training center of this type is in Norway.  The project aims to utilize the soon to be closed mine and it\u2019s already existing facilities and infrastructure. The main coordinator is the city of Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvi with numerous professional partners and businesses, that specialize in fire extinction and safety systems, ICT solutions, and tunnel- and shaft rescue operations. These partners include Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine Oy, Agnico Eagle Finland Oy, Sotkamo Silver AB, Anglo American Sakatti Mining Oy, J&T Technology Oy, M-Solutions Oy and Posiva Oy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://callio.info/2017/wp-content/uploads/Tiedote-25.6.2019.pdf|title=Underground Rescue|last=|first=|date=25 June 2019|website=Mine for Business - Callio|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n=== Pumped Hydroelectric Storage Facility ===\nIt was announced on December 4<sup>th</sup>, 2019 that Pumped Hydro Storage Sweden AB and Callio have signed a co-operation agreement to build a demo model of a [[Pumped-storage hydroelectricity|pumped hydroelectric energy]] storage facility in the Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine. The purpose of this co-operation is to design and develop on a smaller scale a pilot facility which can later be implemented in a full-scale version. Work is already underway, including the technical plans, timetables, and financing of the project.\n\nThis is the first phase of Callio's plans for a pumped hydroelectric storage facility in Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine. Once the creation, testing and optimizing it this demo facility for use is completed, Callio will move to phase two. Phase two aims to negotiate the fulfillment of a full-scale 75MW facility.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businessoulu.com/fi/uutiset/pumppuvesivoimaan-perustuvan-energiavaraston-demolaitos-toteutumassa-pyhajarven-callioon.html|title=Pumppuvesivoimaan perustuvan energiavaraston demolaitos toteutumassa Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rven Callioon|website=www.businessoulu.com|language=FI|access-date=2020-01-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ostologistiikka.fi/kategoriat/teknologia/pyhajarven-pumppuvesivoiman-demolaitos-tekeille|title=Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rven pumppuvesivoiman demolaitos tekeille - Osto&Logistiikka|website=www.ostologistiikka.fi|language=fi|access-date=2020-01-10}}</ref>\n\n== The Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine ==\n\nThe overall depth of the Pyh\u00e4salmi mine is 1450&nbsp;m (4760&nbsp;ft), making it the deepest base metal mine in Europe.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.first-quantum.com/Our-Business/operating-mines/Pyhasalmi/default.aspx|title=Pyh\u00e4salmi Copper mine|last=|first=|date=|website=www.first-quantum.com|language=en-CA|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.euronews.com/2012/05/02/new-life-for-old-metal-mines|title=New life for old metal mines|date=2012-05-02|work=euronews|access-date=2018-03-02|language=en}}</ref> Its main metals are [[copper]] and [[Zinc (element)|zinc]].\n\nThe mine was opened in 1962 by [[Outokumpu]], sold to [[Inmet Mining|Inmet mining]] in 2002, and obtained by [[First Quantum Minerals]] in 2013.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.kaleva.fi/uutiset/pohjois-suomi/pyhasalmen-kaivoksella-haikea-tunnelma/123595/|title=Pyh\u00e4salmen kaivoksella haikea tunnelma|date=December 20, 2001|work=Kaleva.fi|access-date=2018-03-02|language=fi}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://yle.fi/uutiset/3-6551819|title=Kanadalainen kuparij\u00e4tti ostaa my\u00f6s Suomessa toimivan kaivosyhti\u00f6n|last=Harala|first=Samuli|date=March 24, 2013|website=Yle Uutiset|language=fi|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref> The mine was previously planned to close by the end of 2019, but has been granted approximately 14 months more of mining activity due to an increase in demand for [[pyrite]] from [[Yara International|Yara]] in Siilinj\u00e4rvi. Pyrite is a by product of copper and zinc mining. As of now, mining is going to be continued until spring 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://yle.fi/uutiset/3-10888381|title=Pyh\u00e4salmen kaivos sai yli vuoden jatkoajan lannoitetehtaan ansiosta|website=Yle Uutiset|language=fi|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref> Above-ground refinery will continue until 2025.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.kauppalehti.fi/uutiset/yara-ja-pyhasalmen-kaivos-pitkaaikaiseen-sopimukseen-pyriittitoimituksista/fziHDRG6|title=Yara ja Pyh\u00e4salmen kaivos pitk\u00e4aikaiseen sopimukseen pyriittitoimituksista {{!}} Kauppalehti|last=M\u00e4h\u00f6nen|first=Erno|date=August 9, 2016|website=Kauppalehti|language=fi-FI|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref>\n\nThe mine safety has improved significantly over the last decades, and the underground mine has become a test bed for new (often award-winning<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.tekniikkatalous.fi/tekniikka/metalli/2003-09-09/Malminrikastus-sai-automaatiopalkinnon-3267123.html|title=Malminrikastus sai automaatiopalkinnon|date=September 9, 2003|work=Tekniikka & Talous|access-date=2018-03-02|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.tekniikkatalous.fi/arkisto/2006-01-26/Kaivosj%C3%A4rjestelm%C3%A4-sai-automaatiopalkinnon-3282535.html|title=Kaivosj\u00e4rjestelm\u00e4 sai automaatiopalkinnon|date=January 26, 2006|work=Tekniikka & Talous|access-date=2018-03-02|language=en}}</ref>) access control, monitoring and automation technology.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rfidjournal.com/articles/view?12925|title=Pyh\u00e4salmi Mine Will Expand RFID System to Boost Safety|last=Claire Swedberg and Mark Roberti|date=April 8, 2015|website=www.rfidjournal.com|language=en|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/indoor-smartphone-compass-locater|title=Finnish startup can locate you indoors using magnetic field anomalies|last=Clark|first=Liat|date=April 8, 2015|work=Wired Magazine|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.tekniikkatalous.fi/tekniikka/ict/2015-06-01/Ericsson-kokeilee-5G-verkkoja-kaivoksessa---Malmirekka-et%C3%A4ohjaukseen-3321894.html|title=Ericsson kokeilee 5G-verkkoja kaivoksessa - Malmirekka et\u00e4ohjaukseen|last=Ikkala|first=Tapio|date=June 1, 2015|work=Tekniikka & Talous|access-date=2018-03-02|language=en}}</ref> Underground accidents in Pyh\u00e4salmi are very rare, and the last fatality occurred in 1995.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hs.fi/kotimaa/art-2000003446972.html|title=Mies kuoli pudottuaan 60 metri\u00e4 kaivoksessa Pyh\u00e4salmella|last=Marttinen|first=Heikki|date=1995-07-03|work=Helsingin Sanomat|access-date=2018-03-02|language=fi-FI}}</ref> Several easily contained on-ground refinery fires have however occurred at the site during the 2000's.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hs.fi/kotimaa/art-2000004090027.html|title=Palo Pyh\u00e4salmen kaivoksella|date=2002-10-14|work=Helsingin Sanomat|access-date=2018-03-02|language=fi-FI}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.kaleva.fi/uutiset/pohjois-suomi/kaivoksessa-tulipalo/83355/|title=Kaivoksessa tulipalo|date=May 18, 2006|work=Kaleva.fi|access-date=2018-03-02|language=fi}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.kaleva.fi/uutiset/kotimaa/kaivospaloa-sammutettiin-30-metrin-korkeudella-pyhajarvella/169981/|title=Kaivospaloa sammutettiin 30 metrin korkeudella Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvell\u00e4|date=May 22, 2010|work=Kaleva.fi|access-date=2018-03-02|language=fi}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.kaleva.fi/uutiset/kotimaa/pyhasalmen-kaivoksen-tornissa-paloi-sammutustyot-70-metrin-korkeudessa/690837/|title=Pyh\u00e4salmen kaivoksen tornissa paloi - sammutusty\u00f6t 70 metrin korkeudessa|date=March 1, 2015|work=Kaleva.fi|access-date=2018-03-02|language=fi}}</ref> In 2012, explosives contaminated with pyrite ore were sent from the Pyh\u00e4salmi mine for destruction at the Forcit ammunition factory in [[Vihtavuori]], where (after a year in storage) the container started to heat up and smoke.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://yle.fi/uutiset/3-6917325|title=Tukes: Varomattomuus aiheutti Vihtavuoren suuronnettomuusvaaran|last=Pajunen|first=Ilpo|date=November 5, 2013|website=Yle Uutiset|language=fi|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.is.fi/kotimaa/art-2000000677454.html|title=Vihtavuoren onnettomuustutkinnan tulokset julki - t\u00e4m\u00e4 aiheutti suuronnettomuuden vaaran|date=2013-11-05|work=Ilta-Sanomat|access-date=2018-03-02|language=fi-FI}}</ref> The reason for this potentially dangerous situation was revealed to be careless handling and packaging at the mine. This prompted significant changes in the safety protocols, and since 2013 all hazardous waste is destroyed on-site in Pyh\u00e4salmi.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://yle.fi/uutiset/3-6746708|title=Laukaan vaaratilanne johti muutoksiin Pyh\u00e4salmen kaivoksella|last=Karppinen|first=Kirsi|date=July 25, 2013|website=Yle Uutiset|language=fi|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref>\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://callio.info/ Callio website]\n* [https://calliolab.com/ CallioLab website]\n* [https://sketchfab.com/models/689513c4b34f4246ba0b84f5744153a5 3D video of the Callio facilities] at [[Sketchfab]]\n* [http://bsuin.eu/ BSUIN (Baltic Sea Underground Facilities and Innovation Network) website]\n*[http://minetrain.eu/contact.html MINETRAIN] \n\n== References ==\n<!-- Inline citations added to your article will automatically display here. See https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WP:REFB for instructions on how to add citations. -->\n{{reflist}}\n*\n{{Underground laboratories}}\n\n[[Category:Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvi]]\n[[Category:Particle physics facilities]]\n[[Category:Underground laboratories]]\n[[Category:Laboratories in Finland]]\n", "name_user": "Alistair1978", "label": "safe", "comment": "typo (viaWP:JWB)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Callio"}
{"title_page": "Oakland County, Michigan", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2014}}\n{{Infobox U.S. county\n| county = Oakland County\n| state = Michigan\n|type=[[County (United States)|County]]\n|official_name=County of Oakland\n| ex image = Pontiac Commercial Historic District B.JPG\n| ex image size = 250px\n| ex image cap = [[Pontiac Commercial Historic District]]\n| seal = Seal of Oakland County, Michigan.svg\n| founded year = 1819 (created)<br/>1820 (organized)<ref name=\"Clarke\">{{cite web|url=https://www.cmich.edu/library/clarke/AccessMaterials/Bibliographies/MichiganLocalHistory/Pages/oakland.aspx|publisher=[[Clarke Historical Library]], [[Central Michigan University]]|title=Bibliography on Oakland County|accessdate=January 29, 2013|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006084440/https://www.cmich.edu/library/clarke/AccessMaterials/Bibliographies/MichiganLocalHistory/Pages/oakland.aspx|archivedate=October 6, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>[http://oaklandweb.com/govt/county/county_history.htm \"History of Oakland County,\" ''OaklandWeb.com''.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060705102642/http://oaklandweb.com/govt/county/county_history.htm |date=July 5, 2006 }} Retrieved February 7, 2007.</ref>\n| founded date = January 12\n| seat wl = Pontiac\n| largest city wl = Troy\n| area_total_sq_mi = 907\n| area_land_sq_mi = 868\n| area_water_sq_mi = 40\n| area percentage = 4.4\n| census estimate yr = 2018\n| pop = 1,259,201\n| density_sq_mi = 1386\n| time zone = Eastern\n| web = www.oakgov.com\n| district = 8th\n| district2 = 9th\n| district3 = 11th\n| district4 = 14th\n}}\n\n'''Oakland County''' is a [[County (United States)|county]] in the [[U.S. state]] of [[Michigan]]. It is part of the [[Metro Detroit|metropolitan Detroit]] area, located northwest of the city. As of the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]], its population was 1,202,362,<ref name=\"QF\">{{cite web|title=State & County QuickFacts|url=http://quickfacts.census.gov/qfd/states/26/26125.html|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=August 29, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714193415/http://quickfacts.census.gov/qfd/states/26/26125.html|archivedate=July 14, 2011|df=mdy-all}}</ref> making it the second-most populous county in Michigan, behind neighboring [[Wayne County, Michigan|Wayne County]]. The [[county seat]] is [[Pontiac, Michigan|Pontiac]].<ref name=\"GR6\">{{cite web|url=http://www.naco.org/Counties/Pages/FindACounty.aspx |accessdate=June 7, 2011 |title=Find a County |publisher=National Association of Counties |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110531210815/http://www.naco.org/Counties/Pages/FindACounty.aspx |archivedate=May 31, 2011 }}</ref> The county was founded in 1819 and organized in 1820.<ref name=\"Clarke\"/><ref>{{cite book|title=History of Oakland County, Michigan|publisher=L. H. Everts and Co.|place=Philadelphia|date=1877|page=[https://archive.org/details/afk0725.0001.001.umich.edu/page/23 23]|url=https://archive.org/details/afk0725.0001.001.umich.edu|accessdate=October 4, 2014|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151120214645/https://archive.org/details/afk0725.0001.001.umich.edu|archivedate=November 20, 2015|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nOakland County is composed of 62 cities, townships, and villages, and is part of the [[Detroit]]-[[Warren, Michigan|Warren]]-[[Dearborn, Michigan|Dearborn]], MI [[Metro Detroit|Metropolitan Statistical Area]]. The city of Detroit is in neighboring [[Wayne County, Michigan|Wayne County]], south of [[M-102 (Michigan highway)|8 Mile Road]]. Oakland County is among the ten highest income counties in the United States with populations over one million people.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.detroitchamber.com/region/About-Detroit/Quick-Facts/925-population|title=Detroit Regional Chamber of Commerce - quick facts|website=detroitchamber.com|accessdate=April 29, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121010002152/http://www.detroitchamber.com/region/About-Detroit/Quick-Facts/925-population|archivedate=October 10, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref> It is also home to [[Oakland University]], a large public institution that straddles the [[Auburn Hills, Michigan|Auburn Hills]] and [[Rochester Hills, Michigan|Rochester Hills]] border.\n\nThe county's knowledge-based economic initiative, coined \"Automation Alley\", has developed one of the largest employment centers for engineering and related occupations in the United States, and some major employers include [[General Motors Corporation|General Motors]], [[Ford Motor Company|Ford]], and [[Chrysler]], collectively known as the [[Big Three (automobile manufacturers)|Big Three]].\n\n==History==\n{{See also|List of National Historic Landmarks in Michigan|National Register of Historic Places listings in Oakland County, Michigan}}\n\nFounded by Territorial Governor [[Lewis Cass]] in 1819, sparsely settled Oakland was originally twice its current size. As was customary at the time, as populations increased, other counties were organized from its land area. Woodward Avenue and the [[Detroit and Pontiac Railroad]] helped draw settlers in the 1840s. By 1840, Oakland had more than fifty lumber mills, processing wood harvested from the region and the Upper Peninsula. Pontiac, located on the [[Clinton River (Michigan)|Clinton River]], was Oakland's first town and became the county seat. After the Civil War, Oakland was still primarily a rural, agricultural county with numerous isolated villages. By the end of the 19th century, three rail lines served Pontiac, and the city attracted carriage and wagon factories. In the late 1890s streetcars were constructed here and to Detroit.{{citation needed|date=December 2016}}\n\nAt that time, developers made southern Oakland County a suburb of Detroit; a Cincinnati firm platted a section of Royal Oak called \"Urbanrest.\" Migration worked both ways. Several thousand people moved from Oakland County farms to Detroit as the city attracted factories. By 1910, a number of rich [[Detroit]]ers had summer homes and some year-round residences in what became Bloomfield Hills. The auto age enveloped Pontiac in the early 1900s. The [[Oakland (automobile)|Oakland Motor Car Company]] was founded in 1907 and became a part of General Motors Corp., which was soon Pontiac's dominant firm.{{citation needed|date=December 2016}}\n\nIn the 1950s, the Detroit metropolitan population began migrating to the suburbs, aided by the GI Bill for veterans and federal subsidies for highways and freeways.{{citation needed|date=December 2016}} Oakland County is among the ten highest-income counties in the United States with more than one million population.{{citation needed|date=December 2016}} The median price of a home in Oakland County increased to $164,697, more than $30,000 above the national median. Oakland County is home to popular super-regional shopping malls such as [[Somerset Collection]], [[Twelve Oaks Mall]], and [[Great Lakes Crossing Outlets]].{{citation needed|date=December 2016}}\n\nOn March 10, 2020, Michigan reported the first 2 coronavirus cases, one of which was in Oakland County.\n\n==Geography==\nAccording to the [[U.S. Census Bureau]], the county has a total area of {{convert|907|sqmi}}, of which {{convert|868|sqmi}} is land and {{convert|40|sqmi}} (4.4%) is water.<ref name=\"GR1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/geo/maps-data/data/docs/gazetteer/counties_list_26.txt|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=September 27, 2014|date=August 22, 2012|title=2010 Census Gazetteer Files|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131113024015/http://www.census.gov/geo/maps-data/data/docs/gazetteer/counties_list_26.txt|archivedate=November 13, 2013|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nOakland County was originally divided into 25 separate [[townships]], which are listed below. Each township is roughly equal in size at six miles (10&nbsp;km) by six miles, for a total township area of {{convert|36|sqmi|km2}}.  The roots of this design were born out of the [[Land Ordinance of 1785]] and the subsequent [[Northwest Ordinance]] of 1787.  Oakland County itself is a prime example of the land policy that was established, as all townships are equal in size (save for slight variations due to waterways).  Section 16 in each township was reserved for financing and maintaining public education, and even today many schools in Oakland County townships are located within that section.\n\n[[Wayne County, Michigan|Wayne County]], where the city of [[Detroit, Michigan|Detroit]] is located, borders Oakland County to the south. [[8 Mile Road]], also known as \"Baseline Road\" in some areas, is the boundary between these counties.  The baseline was used during the original surveying for Michigan, and it serves as the northern/southern boundaries for counties from [[Lake Saint Clair (North America)|Lake St. Clair]] to [[Lake Michigan]]. As more working and middle-class populations moved to the suburbs from the 1950s on, this divide (8 Mile Road) became historically known as an unofficial racial dividing line between what became the predominantly [[Black people|black]] city and almost exclusively [[whites|white]] suburbs.\n\nSince the late 20th century, however, the patterns of ''de facto'' [[Racial segregation|segregation]] have faded as the suburbs have become more diverse. Middle-class African Americans have left the city, settling in inner-ring suburbs, notably Southfield (75.08%), west of [[M-1 (Michigan highway)|Woodward Avenue]]. Based on the 2010 Census, the following cities also have significant minority ethnic populations: Farmington (25.3%), Farmington Hills (31.7%), Novi (30.12%), [[Oak Park, Michigan|Oak Park]] (62.61%), Lathrup Village (72.97%), Orchard Lake Village (16.08%), Rochester Hills (20.94%), Troy (29.4%), Wixom (26.28%), West Bloomfield (24.0%), Bloomfield (18.28%), Bloomfield Hills (14.2%), [[Ferndale, Michigan|Ferndale]] (17.2%), and Madison Heights (17.7%). Ferndale has a concentration of [[Arab Americans]], who also live in nearby areas, and numerous [[Asian Americans]], particularly [[India]]ns, have also settled in these areas.\n\n===Adjacent counties===\n*[[Lapeer County, Michigan|Lapeer County]] (northeast)\n*[[Genesee County, Michigan|Genesee County]] (northwest)\n*[[Macomb County, Michigan|Macomb County]] (east)\n*[[Wayne County, Michigan|Wayne County]] (southeast)\n*[[Washtenaw County, Michigan|Washtenaw County]] (southwest)\n*[[Livingston County, Michigan|Livingston County]] (west)\n\n==Demographics==\n{{US Census population\n|1820= 330\n|1830= 4911\n|1840= 23646\n|1850= 31270\n|1860= 38261\n|1870= 40867\n|1880= 41537\n|1890= 41245\n|1900= 44792\n|1910= 49576\n|1920= 90050\n|1930= 211251\n|1940= 254068\n|1950= 396001\n|1960= 690259\n|1970= 907871\n|1980= 1011793\n|1990= 1083592\n|2000= 1194156\n|2010= 1202362\n|estyear=2018\n|estimate=1259201\n|estref=<ref name=\"USCensusEst2018\">{{citeweb|url=https://factfinder.census.gov/faces/nav/jsf/pages/community_facts.xhtml|title=QuickFacts|accessdate=April 18, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110717015826/http://quickfacts.census.gov/qfd/states/16/16055.html|archive-date=July 17, 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|align-fn=center\n|footnote=U.S. Decennial Census<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/prod/www/decennial.html|title=U.S. Decennial Census|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=September 27, 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150426102944/http://www.census.gov/prod/www/decennial.html|archivedate=April 26, 2015|df=mdy-all}}</ref><br />1790-1960<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mapserver.lib.virginia.edu|title=Historical Census Browser|publisher=University of Virginia Library|accessdate=September 27, 2014|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120811110448/http://mapserver.lib.virginia.edu/|archivedate=August 11, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref> 1900-1990<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/population/cencounts/mi190090.txt|title=Population of Counties by Decennial Census: 1900 to 1990|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=September 27, 2014|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150215142038/http://www.census.gov/population/cencounts/mi190090.txt|archivedate=February 15, 2015|df=mdy-all}}</ref><br />1990-2000<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/population/www/cen2000/briefs/phc-t4/tables/tab02.pdf|title=Census 2000 PHC-T-4. Ranking Tables for Counties: 1990 and 2000|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=September 27, 2014|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141218203824/http://www.census.gov/population/www/cen2000/briefs/phc-t4/tables/tab02.pdf|archivedate=December 18, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref> 2010-2018<ref name=\"QF\"/>\n}}\n\nAs of the [[2010 United States Census|2010 Census]], there were 1,202,362 people and 315,175 families residing in the county. 77.3% were [[White American|White]], 13.6% [[African American|Black or African American]], 5.6% [[Asian American|Asian]], 0.3% [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 1.0% of some other race and 2.2% [[Multiracial American|of two or more races]]. 3.5% were [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] (of any race). There were 527,255 housing units at an average density of 564 per square mile (218/km\u00b2).<ref name=\"U.S. Census State and County Quick Facts\">{{cite web |url=http://quickfacts.census.gov/qfd/states/26/26125.html |title=Oakland County QuickFacts from the US Census Bureau |url-status=dead |accessdate=July 6, 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714193415/http://quickfacts.census.gov/qfd/states/26/26125.html |archivedate=July 14, 2011 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\nRegarding ancestry, in 2000 14.4% of the population were ethnically [[Germans|German]], 9.0% [[Irish people|Irish]], 8.5% [[English people|English]], 8.5% [[poles|Polish]], 5.7% [[Italians|Italian]] and 5.5% [[United States|American]], 87.4% spoke only [[English language|English]] at home; 2.0% spoke [[Spanish language|Spanish]], 1.3% [[Syriac language|Syriac (Neo Aramaic)]] and 1.0% [[Arabic language|Arabic]].  The [[population density]] as of the [[2000 United States Census|2000 census]] was 1,369 people per square mile (528/km\u00b2). There were 492,006 housing units at an average density of 564 per square mile (218/km\u00b2).\n\nThe 2000 census showed two Native American tribes with more than 1,000 members in Oakland County.  There were 2,095 Cherokee and 1,458 Chippewa.\n\nThe Jewish community of metropolitan Detroit, with a population of 72,000, is the 21st largest Jewish community in the nation.  This community is concentrated in Oakland County, especially in West Bloomfield, Bloomfield Hills, Farmington Hills, Troy and Huntington Woods.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://detroitjcrc.org/community_relations/detroit.php?page=10080 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-08-04 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110725231357/http://detroitjcrc.org/community_relations/detroit.php?page=10080 |archivedate=July 25, 2011 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\nThere were 471,115 households, of which 32.40% had children under the age of 18 living with them.  54.20% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 9.50% had a female householder with no husband present, and 33.10% were non-families. 27.30% of all households were made up of individuals and 8.50% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.51 and the average family size was 3.09.\n\nAmong Asian Americans, eight ethnic groups had more than 1,000 members in the county in 2000. The most numerous were those of [[Indian American|Asian Indian]] descent, with 20,705. Next were those of [[Chinese American|Chinese]] heritage, numbering 10,018. Next were those of [[Japanese American|Japanese]] (5,589), [[Filipino American|Filipino]] (5,450) [[Korean American|Korean]] (5,351), [[Vietnamese American|Vietnamese]] (1,687), [[Pakistani American|Pakistani]] (1,458) and [[Hmong people|Hmong]] (1,210) ancestry.<ref name=\"search results\">See [http://factfinder.census.gov/servlet/DTTable?_bm=y&-context=dt&-ds_name=DEC_2000_SF1_U&-CONTEXT=dt&-mt_name=DEC_2000_SF1_U_PCT007&-mt_name=DEC_2000_SF1_U_PCT010&-mt_name=DEC_2000_SF1_U_PCT011&-mt_name=DEC_2000_SF1_U_PCT003&-tree_id=4001&-redoLog=true&-all_geo_types=N&-_caller=geoselect&-geo_id=05000US26099&-geo_id=05000US26125&-geo_id=05000US26127&-geo_id=05000US26163&-search_results=01000US&-format=&-_lang=en search results] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110608174512/http://factfinder.census.gov/servlet/DTTable?_bm=y&-context=dt&-ds_name=DEC_2000_SF1_U&-CONTEXT=dt&-mt_name=DEC_2000_SF1_U_PCT007&-mt_name=DEC_2000_SF1_U_PCT010&-mt_name=DEC_2000_SF1_U_PCT011&-mt_name=DEC_2000_SF1_U_PCT003&-tree_id=4001&-redoLog=true&-all_geo_types=N&-_caller=geoselect&-geo_id=05000US26099&-geo_id=05000US26125&-geo_id=05000US26127&-geo_id=05000US26163&-search_results=01000US&-format=&-_lang=en |date=June 8, 2011 }} from ''[[United States Census Bureau]]''. Retrieved July 2, 2007.</ref>\n\nIn 2001, Oakland County had the 36th largest Asian population of any county in the country.<ref>Metzger, Kurt and Jason Booza. \"[http://www.cus.wayne.edu/content/publications/Asians7.pdf Asians in the United States, Michigan and Metropolitan Detroit] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131109050601/http://www.cus.wayne.edu/content/publications/Asians7.pdf |date=November 9, 2013 }}.\" [[Wayne State University]] Center for Urban Studies-January 2001 Working Paper Series, No. 7, p. 5. Retrieved on September 8, 2013.</ref> In 2002, of the Oakland-[[Wayne County, Michigan|Wayne]]-[[Macomb County, Michigan|Macomb]] tricounty area, Oakland County had 49% of the tri-county area's Asian population.<ref>Metzger, Kurt and Jason Booza. \"[http://www.cus.wayne.edu/content/publications/Asians7.pdf Asians in the United States, Michigan and Metropolitan Detroit] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131109050601/http://www.cus.wayne.edu/content/publications/Asians7.pdf |date=November 9, 2013 }}.\" Center for Urban Studies, [[Wayne State University]]. January 2002 Working Paper Series, No. 7. p. 7. Retrieved on November 6, 2013.</ref>\n\nThe county's population was spread out in terms of age, with 25.20% of people under the age of 18, 7.20% from 18 to 24, 32.40% from 25 to 44, 23.90% from 45 to 64, and 11.30% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 37 years. For every 100 females, there were 95.90 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 92.70 males.\n\nThe median income for a household in the county was $86,567, making Oakland County the 21st wealthiest county in the United States: (http://www.worldatlas.com/articles/richest-counties-in-the-united-states.html). Males had a median income of $55,833 versus $35,890 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the county was $65,759. About 3.80% of families and 5.50% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 6.50% of those under age 18 and 6.50% of those age 65 or over.\n\n==Government==\n{{More citations needed section|date=February 2012}}\n\nThe county government operates the [[County jail|jail]], operates the major local courts, keeps files of deeds and mortgages, maintains [[vital records]], administers [[public health]] regulations, and participates with the state in the provision of welfare and other social services. The [[county commission|county board of commissioners]] controls the budget but has limited authority to make laws or ordinances. In Michigan, most local government functions&mdash;police and fire, building and zoning, tax assessment, street maintenance, etc. &mdash; are the responsibility of individual cities and townships. Oakland County has an elected sheriff, and his or her law-enforcement services are used throughout the county. Fourteen cities/townships do not have municipal police forces, but rather contract with the sheriff for police services specific to the municipalities. For instance, the city of Rochester Hills does not have a \"Rochester Hills Police Department,\" but instead has an established sheriff substation in the city with deputies who are dedicated to that city only. That branch operates as the Oakland County Sheriff's Department, Rochester Hills substation. The sheriff operates in the same manner with other municipalities who opt not to have their own police agencies. This typically is a cost-effective way for municipalities to provide police services to its citizens.  The county sheriff also maintains a civil division, marine division, alcohol and traffic enforcement units, and an aviation division.\n\n===Elected officials===\n* [[County Executive]]: [[David Coulter (politician)|Dave Coulter]] (Democrat){{ref|a}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.freep.com/story/news/politics/2019/08/03/l-brooks-patterson-oakland-county-gerald-poisson/1909186001/|title=L. Brooks Patterson's successor as Oakland County executive|first=Bill|last=Laitner|website=Detroit Free Press}}</ref>\n* [[Prosecutor|Prosecuting Attorney]]: [[Jessica R. Cooper]] (Democrat)<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.detnews.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20090115/METRO/901150398|title=New Oakland prosecutor 'going pretty hard'|last=Martindale|first=Mike|date=January 15, 2009|newspaper=The Detroit News|accessdate=March 1, 2009}}</ref>\n* [[Sheriff]]: [[Mike Bouchard]] (Republican)\n* [[County Clerk]]/[[Register of Deeds]]: [[Lisa Brown (Michigan politician)|Lisa Brown]] (Democrat)\n* [[Treasurer|County Treasurer]]: [[Andy Meisner]] (Democrat)\n* [[Water Resources Commissioner]]: [[James H. Nash|Jim Nash]] (Democrat)\n* [[County Commission|Board of Commissioners]]: 21 members, elected from districts (11 Democrats, 10 Republicans)\n\n<small>(information as of August 4, 2019)</small>\n\n===Road Commission===\nRoads that are not maintained by a local community (city/village) are maintained by the independent Road Commission for Oakland County, which is governed by three board members appointed by the Oakland County Board of Commissioners.\nRoad Commissioners:  Eric. S. Wilson, Chairman; Gregory C. Jamian Vice Chairman; Ron Fowkes\nDennis G. Kolar, Managing Director\n\n===Oakland County Service Center===\nThe East Campus of the Oakland County Service Center is located in [[Pontiac, Michigan|Pontiac]]. It includes the county courthouse and jail for adults.<ref name=Complexmap>\"[https://www.oakgov.com/maps/Documents/occomplexmap.pdf Complex Map]\" ({{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150710032719/https://www.oakgov.com/maps/Documents/occomplexmap.pdf |date=2015-07-10 }}). Oakland County Government. Retrieved on July 9, 2015.</ref>\n\nThe West Campus of the Oakland County Service Center is located in [[Waterford Township, Michigan|Waterford Township]].<ref name=Complexmap/><ref>\"[http://twp.waterford.mi.us/Departments/GIS-and-Online-Mapping/Documents/Generic-Base-Map-2014.aspx Generic Base Map 2014]\" ({{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150113150851/http://twp.waterford.mi.us/Departments/GIS-and-Online-Mapping/Documents/Generic-Base-Map-2014.aspx |date=2015-01-13 }}). [[Waterford Township, Michigan|Waterford Township]]. Retrieved on July 10, 2015.</ref> This includes the Oakland County Executive Building and Conference Center,<ref>\"[https://www.oakgov.com/advantageoakland/media-center/Documents/Maps/map_eob.pdf Oakland County Executive Office Building Conference Center Locator Map & Directions]\" ({{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150710114738/https://www.oakgov.com/advantageoakland/media-center/Documents/Maps/map_eob.pdf |date=2015-07-10 }}). Oakland County Government. Retrieved on July 10, 2015.</ref> and the Oakland County Children's Village,<ref name=Complexmap/> the county's [[juvenile detention center]] for children.<ref>\"[https://www.oakgov.com/village Oakland County Children's Village]\" ({{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150710014343/https://www.oakgov.com/village |date=2015-07-10 }}). The Government of Oakland County. Retrieved on July 9, 2015. \"Oakland County Children's Village 1200 North Telegraph Road Pontiac, MI 48341\"</ref> The Children's Village acts as one of the support sites for the [[Waterford School District]].<ref>\"[http://www.waterford.k12.mi.us/NorthstarMedia/download/97671?token=OCaRojCyVwc%3d District Map]\" ( {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150904112756/http://www.waterford.k12.mi.us/NorthstarMedia/download/97671?token=OCaRojCyVwc%3d |date=September 4, 2015 }}). [[Waterford School District]]. Retrieved on July 9, 2015.</ref>\n\n==Politics==\nOakland County was historically a classic bastion of suburban conservatism, and was hence a longstanding stronghold of the [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican Party]]. However, since the 1990s it has become more competitive and has voted for the Democratic candidate for President in the last six elections.\n\nIn 1996, Bill Clinton became the first Democrat to secure the plurality of Oakland County presidential votes since Lyndon Johnson in 1964, and only the fourth to do so since 1892. Al Gore and John Kerry also carried the county, by narrow margins, against George W. Bush in 2000 and 2004, respectively. In 2008, Barack Obama became the first Democrat to win a majority in the county since Lyndon Johnson in 1964. (''See table at right''.) He again carried the county in 2012, though by a smaller margin.\n\nWhile the Democratic Party has found increasing success in Presidential elections in Oakland County, the state Republican Party has remained strong in recent gubernatorial and state elections. The county favored Governor [[Rick Snyder]] (R) by a 22-percent margin in the [http://results.enr.clarityelections.com/MI/Oakland/22923/42960/en/summary.html 2010] statewide elections and again by a 12-point margin in [http://results.enr.clarityelections.com/MI/Oakland/54212/149511/en/summary.html 2014]. While Republicans held a majority on the County Commission for most of its history, following the 2018 elections, there are 11 Democrats and 10 Republicans.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theoaklandpress.com/news/elections/oakland-county-board-of-commissioners-majority-democratic-for-third-time/article_04063cb6-e2a4-11e8-b25c-530fb554a487.html|title=Oakland County Board of Commissioners majority Democratic for third time in history|last=Cavitt|first=Mark|date=November 7, 2018|publisher=[[The Oakland Press]]|accessdate=March 30, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn the [[116th United States Congress|116th Congress]], Oakland County is represented by four Democrats, [[Brenda Lawrence]] ([[Michigan's 14th congressional district|14th]]), [[Andy Levin]] ([[Michigan's 9th congressional district|9th]]), [[Haley Stevens]] ([[Michigan's 11th congressional district|11th]]) and [[Elissa Slotkin]] ([[Michigan's 8th congressional district|8th]]). Slotkin and Stevens were first elected in 2018, flipping Republican-held seats.\n\n{{Hidden begin\n|titlestyle = background:#ccccff;\n|title      = Presidential election results\n}}\n{| align=\"center\" border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"float:right; margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|+ '''Presidential election results'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uselectionatlas.org/RESULTS|title=Dave Leip's Atlas of U.S. Presidential Elections|first=David|last=Leip|website=uselectionatlas.org|accessdate=April 29, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180323225526/https://uselectionatlas.org/RESULTS/|archivedate=March 23, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n|- bgcolor=lightgrey\n! Year\n! [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n! [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]\n! [[Third Party (United States)|Third Parties]]\n|-\n|  style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/D