ust 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2018\n| ''[[iZombie (TV series)|iZombie]]\n| Himself (voice cameo)\n| Episode: \"[[List of iZombie episodes#ep58|And He Shall Be A Good Man]]\"; uncredited\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | <ref>{{cite web |first1=Jenna |last1=Anderson |title='iZombie': 7 Questions Raised by the Season 4 Finale |url=https://comicbook.com/dc/2018/05/29/izombie-season-4-finale-episode-liv-major-ravi-clive/#3 |publisher=Comicbook.com |accessdate=January 16, 2020|date=29 May 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2019\n| ''[[Living with Yourself]]\n| Miles Elliot\n| Also executive producer\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | <ref>{{cite web | first1=Libby |last1=Hill |title=Paul Rudd and the \u2018Living With Yourself\u2019 Directors Share Their Key Behind-the-Scenes Secrets |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2019/11/paul-rudd-living-with-yourself-season-2-netflix-podcast-millions-of-screens-episode-6-1202191068/ |publisher=[[IndieWire]] |accessdate=January 16, 2020 |date=20 November 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2021\n| ''[[What If...? (TV series)|What If...?]]''\n| Scott Lang / Ant-Man (voice)\n| Guest role; In voice recording process\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | <ref>{{cite web |title=Ant-Man himself, Paul Rudd, plays real-life superhero; helps women with luggage, poses for selfies at NYC airport |url=https://www.live955.com/ant-man-himself-paul-rudd-plays-real-life-superhero-helps-women-with-luggage-poses-for-selfies-at-nyc-airport/ |publisher=[[Alpha Media]] |accessdate=January 16, 2020 |date=12 September 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n*{{main|List of awards and nominations received by Paul Rudd}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|0748620|Paul Rudd}}\n* {{amg name|225541|Paul Rudd}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rudd, Paul}}\n[[Category:Male actor filmographies]]\n[[Category:American filmographies]]\n", "text_old": "{{more citations needed|date=September 2017}}\n[[File:Paul Rudd (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright=1.3|alt=Headshot of Paul Rudd looking off camera and smiling|June 2015]]\n\n\n[[Paul Rudd]] is an American actor, comedian, writer, and producer whose career began in 1992 when he was cast in the role of Kirby Philby in the TV series ''[[Sisters (American TV series)|Sisters]]'' until 1995. Also in 1995, he co-starred alongside [[Alicia Silverstone]] in the [[cult film|cult classic]] ''[[Clueless (film)|Clueless]]'', one of his more notable early roles.<ref>{{cite web |first1=Hazel| last1=Cills |title=Why 'Clueless' Is Still the Ultimate Teen Comedy |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/movie-news/why-clueless-is-still-the-ultimate-teen-comedy-114631/ |website=[[Rolling Stone]] |accessdate=January 7, 2020 |date= July 15, 2015}}</ref> The following year he played [[Count Paris|Dave Paris]] in [[Baz Luhrmann]]'s ''[[Romeo + Juliet]]'' with [[Claire Danes]]. In the 2000's, he co-starred in ''[[Wet Hot American Summer]]'' with [[Janeane Garofalo]] (2001), ''[[P.S. (film)|P.S.]]'' with [[Laura Linney]] (2004), and starred in ''[[Role Models]]'' with [[Seann William Scott]] (2008) and ''[[I Love You, Man]]'' with [[Jason Segel]] (2009). Rudd has appeared in numerous films directed and produced by [[Judd Apatow]] whom he frequently collaborates with including ''[[Anchorman: The Legend of Ron Burgundy]]'' (2004), ''[[The 40-Year-Old Virgin]]'' (2005), ''[[Knocked Up]]'' (2007), ''[[Forgetting Sarah Marshall]]'' (2008), ''[[This Is 40]]'' (2012), and ''[[Anchorman 2: The Legend Continues]]'' (2013).\n\nSince 2015, Rudd has played [[Scott Lang (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Scott Lang / Ant-Man]] in the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]], appearing in ''[[Ant-Man (film)|Ant-Man]]'' (2015), ''[[Captain America: Civil War]]'' (2016), ''[[Ant-Man and the Wasp]]'' (2018), ''[[Avengers: Endgame]]'' (2019) and will voice him again in the 2021 series ''[[What If...? (TV series)|What If...?]]''.\n\nIn addition to his film career, Rudd has appeared in numerous television shows, including the NBC sitcom ''[[Friends]]'' as [[List of recurring characters in Friends#Mike Hannigan|Mike Hannigan]], along with guest roles on ''[[Tim and Eric Awesome Show, Great Job!]]'' and ''[[Parks and Recreation]]'' (as businessman [[Characters of Parks and Recreation#Bobby Newport|Bobby Newport]]) and hosting ''[[Saturday Night Live]]''. He reprised the role of Andy in the follow up series to the [[Wet Hot American Summer|film]] in ''[[Wet Hot American Summer: First Day of Camp]]'' (2015) and ''[[Wet Hot American Summer: Ten Years Later]]'' (2017). In 2019, he starred in the [[Netflix]] series ''[[Living with Yourself]]'' as Miles Elliot.\n\n==Film==\n[[File:Paul Rudd LF.JPG|thumb|upright=1|alt=headshot of Paul Rudd not smiling|December 2007]]\n\n<!-- Please note: do NOT add \"rowspans\" per WP:FILMOGRAPHY -->\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"margin-right: 0;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Role\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{Tooltip|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 1995\n| ''[[Clueless (film)|Clueless]]''\n| Josh\n|\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | <ref>{{cite web |first1=Ashley|last1= Hoffman |title=Clueless Director Reveals How She Discovered Paul Rudd |url=https://time.com/4481070/clueless-paul-rudd-amy-heckerling-interview/ |website=[[Time (magazine)|Time]] |accessdate= January 7, 2020 |language=en |date= September 7, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 1995\n| ''[[Halloween: The Curse of Michael Myers]]''\n| Tommy Doyle\n| Credited as Paul Stephen Rudd\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |  <ref>{{cite web |first1=James |last1=White |title=Anthony Michael Hall Playing Tommy Doyle In Halloween Kills |url=https://www.empireonline.com/movies/news/anthony-michael-hall-tommy-doyle-halloween-paul-rudd/ |website=[[Empire (film magazine)|Empire]] |accessdate=January 7, 2020 |language=en |date= August 26, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 1996\n|